===Etymology===
From {{suffix|lager|phone}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{Australia}} A bush musical ([[percussion]]) instrument consisting of [[crown cap]] beer bottle tops loosely nailed to a pole (often a broom handle) or to a board mounted cross-ways on a pole, and played by striking the pole on the ground or with a stick to rattle the bottle tops.<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/arts/adlib/stories/s915488.htm ABC » Australia adlib (description)]</ref><ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/arts/adlib/stories/s916156.htm ABC » Australia adlib (photograph)]</ref>
